Date: Fri, 18 Aug 2017 13:22:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] arm: 1021a: loop PSCI in according to 1cd9f320

According to 1cd9f320, PSCI is supported by 1021A, so we select
it by Kconfig. Otherwise, this also might affect how many cores
shown online in smp system.

Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig b/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
index 9d03321..7ebdc31 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-imx/Kconfig
@@ -617,6 +617,7 @@ config SOC_LS1021A
 	bool "Freescale LS1021A support"
 	select ARM_GIC
 	select ARCH_HAS_CPUFREQ
+	select ARM_PSCI
 	select HAVE_ARM_ARCH_TIMER
 	select PCI_DOMAINS if PCI
 	select ZONE_DMA if ARM_LPAE
